line_1: Hope's vivid ray her cheerful heart expands:
line_2: The purple hills, and distant rising lands,

line_1: No! blest by Thee, the soul expands,
Glides the quick wheel, the plaistic clay expands,
Turns his quick ears, his webbed claws expands,
line_2: — Her playful Sea-horse woos her soft commands,

line_1: Whence in bright floods the VITAL AIR expands,
line_2: And with concentric spheres involves the lands;

line_1: Incumbent Spring her beamy plumes expands
line_2: O'er restless oceans, and impatient lands,

line_1: Sweet blooms the Rose, the towering Oak expands,
line_2: The Grace and Guard of Britain's golden lands.
Power's rigid heart, and opes his clenching hands;

line_1: If from lone cliffs a bursting rill expands
line_2: Its transient course, and sinks into the sands;
To want, to worth, her ever-loaded hands.
